Problem
I had a scenario where a single data model needed to support multiple valid configurations, but:
Each configuration had different required fields
Some fields were mutually exclusive
Using a single constructor would lead to:
Too many optional parameters
Invalid object states
Excessive null checks
==============================================================

Naive Approach (What Goes Wrong)
class Task {
  final String? userId;
  final String? referenceId;
  final String type;

  Task({
    required this.type,
    this.userId,
    this.referenceId,
  });
}
Problems:
Allows invalid combinations:
type = A but userId = null
type = B but both fields provided
Validation shifts to runtime
Harder to maintain and debug
